<textBlocks>
	<container id="formVBox">
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="25.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Step 1. Get a core team together">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="In this step, you will identify whom to invite to be on the ERB core team, how to recruit them, and what roles they can fill.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Why do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;Going through the ERB process works best when you have a team of 5 to 7 people to make decisions and carry out the activities. A core team that is representative of local constituencies and has a voice in decisions is central to an equitable ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="ERB process"
			linkType="internalIntro"
			link="1">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=".">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Who should be on your core team?: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;It depends on your community's demographic composition, how city and county agencies are organized, who is working on related topics, who works well together, and who has time to be an active contributor.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="How to do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;You can use our ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="recruitment guide"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="Ch1_Core_team_recruitment_guide.docx">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=" to identify possible participants. The guide also contains a template for a recruitment email and a one-page introduction to the ERB process you can attach. Once your team is in place, you can fill in the team section of the ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="project plan"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="Ch1_Project_Plan_Template.docx">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=". During your first meetings, we recommend establishing procedures for how the group will make decisions and what roles everyone will play, and doing a ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="team storytelling activity"
			linkType="internalStep"
			link="0000001">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=". Pro tip: you can always add new team members if you later find there are key gaps to fill.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
